<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<section xml:id="past_quizzes" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Past Quizzes</title>
    <subsection xml:id="quiz_1">
        <title>Quiz 1</title>
        <p><alert>Topic(s): Factoring, GCD/LCM, Distance and Midpoint Formulas, Solving Linear Equations</alert></p>
        <p>
        <ol>
            <li> Solve the following linear equation.
<me>\dfrac{3}{8}+\dfrac{13x}{6}=\dfrac{7x}{4}+1</me></li>
            <li> Factor each of the integers below completely.
<m>m=56 \hspace{1in} n=210</m></li>
            <li> Find all of the divisors of <m>210</m>.</li>
            <li> Use your factorizations in the previous problem to find the greatest common divisor and least common multiple of the two integers, 
<m>GCD($56,210$)</m> and <m>LCM($56,210$)</m>.</li>
            <li> 	\item Find the distance between the two points below.  Approximate your answer to the nearest tenth.
<me>P$(4,-3)$ \qquad\qquad\qquad Q$(1,-4)$</me></li>
            <li> Find the midpoint of the line between the two points below.
<me>A(-6,-7/2) \qquad\qquad\qquad B(3,5)</me></li>
            <li> Identify the quadrant number (I,II,III, or IV) that the midpoint found in the previous problem is located in.</li>
        </ol>
        </p>
    </subsection>   
</section>